Key Match Events: Edward Cabrera was scratched from his start due to migraine-like symptoms.
The Marlins lost to the Phillies with a score of 16-2.
Austin Kitchen surrendered seven runs over two innings in his fourth MLB outing.
The Marlins allowed 16 runs and 22 hits, both season highs.
Post-Match Reflections: Marlins manager Skip Schumaker expressed relief that Edward Cabrera was out of the hospital and might be able to start in the series finale.
Schumaker reflected on the challenges faced by the Marlins' makeshift rotation throughout the season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ryan Weathers and Braxton Garrett began rehab assignments with Single-A Jupiter and could return before the end of the season.
